p10
(lp11
S'earlier the qutub shahi rulers patronized persianate culture, but eventually adopted the regional culture of the deccan, symbolized by the telugu language and the newly developed deccani idiom of urdu became prominent. although telugu was not their mother tongue, the golconda rulers spoke and wrote telugu, and patronized telugu so exclusively they were termed the "telugu sultans". ibrahim quli was thoroughly acquainted with telugu aesthetics.\n'
