p26
(lp27
S'machilipatnam was developed as a trade center and a thriving market particularly of diamonds was developed nearby the golconda fort, the work force involved in the diamond trading was up to 100,00 people. out of 38 diamond mines of india, 23 were located in the golconda sultanate. the top four pink diamonds of the world are from golconda. magnificent diamonds were taken from the mines in the region surrounding golconda, including the daria-i-noor or "sea of light", at 185 carats, the largest and finest diamond of the crown jewels of iran. the golkonda fort used to have a vault where once the famous koh-i-noor and hope diamonds were stored along with other diamonds.'
